canApprove(uint256,address).details: The function assumes the queried proposal exists.

params._account: The address of the user to check.

returns._0: Returns true if the account is allowed to vote.

params._proposalId: The ID of the proposal to be checked.

returns._0: True if the proposal can be executed, false otherwise.

params._approveProposal: If `true`, the sender will approve the proposal.
params._destinationActionsHash: The hash of the serialized actions that will be executed after the proposal passes.
params._destinationPlugin: The address of the plugin to forward the proposal to when it passes.
params._encryptedPayloadURI: The URI where the encrypted contents of the proposal can be found.
params._publicMetadataUriHash: The hash of the metadata IPFS URI that will be published on the optimistic proposal.

params._actions: the list of actions to execute.
params._metadataUri: An IPFS URI pointing to the public content URI.
params._proposalId: The ID of the proposal to be executed.

returns.destinationActionsHash: The hash of the actions to be executed by the destination plugin after the proposal passes.
returns.destinationPlugin: The address of the plugin where the proposal will be forwarded to when executed.
returns.encryptedPayloadURI: The URI at which the corresponding encrypted data data can be found.
returns.executed: Whether the proposal is executed or not.
returns.parameters: The parameters of the proposal vote.
returns.publicMetadataUriHash: The hash of the metadata IPFS URI to create on the optimistic plugin if the proposal passes.

params._account: The account address to be checked.

returns._0: The vote option cast by a voter for a certain proposal.
The address of the implementation contract.

initialize(address,(bool,uint16,address,.details: This method is required to support [ERC-1822](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1822).

params._dao: The IDAO interface of the associated DAO.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

returns._0: Returns `true` if the interface is supported.

upgradeTo(address).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

UPDATE_MULTISIG_SETTINGS_PERMISSION_ID().notice: The ID of the permission required to call the `addAddresses` and `removeAddresses` functions.

UPGRADE_PLUGIN_PERMISSION_ID().notice: The ID of the permission required to call the `_authorizeUpgrade` function.

approve(uint256).notice: Approves and, optionally, executes the proposal.

canApprove(uint256,address).notice: Checks if an account can participate on a proposal vote. This can be because the vote - was executed, or - the approver is not listed or appointed.

canExecute(uint256).notice: Checks if a proposal can be executed.

constructor.notice: Disables the initializers on the implementation contract to prevent it from being left uninitialized.

getProposal(uint256).notice: Returns all information for a proposal vote by its ID.

hasApproved(uint256,address).notice: Returns whether the account has approved the proposal. Note, that this does not check if the account is listed.

hashActions((address,uint256,bytes)[]).notice: Computes the hash of the given list of actions

implementation().notice: Returns the address of the implementation contract in the [proxy storage slot](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1967) slot the [UUPS proxy](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1822) is pointing to.

lastMultisigSettingsChange().notice: Keeps track at which block number the multisig settings have been changed the last time.

proposalCount().notice: Returns the proposal count determining the next proposal ID.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Checks if this or the parent contract supports an interface by its ID.
